The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.



The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.



The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

title: For Sale:  Beretta carbine 45acp
location: Martin county, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent:
I consider this a loaded Beretta 45 carbine. Sierra Pappa recoil kit, so all the plastic has been replaced. 2 sierra pappa 16rnd mags (these go for $100 each, plus you gotta wait). Sig tac 3× scope red/green, this is a small/light unit with a tactical reticle. Best option because if the batteries die, you still have the black reticle like a normal scope. 2 standard mags and the factory carrying case, which is an excellent hard plastic case. 2 stock extentions for people with longer arms. 

TRIGGER. ....as everyone knows, they are crap from the factory. Unbelievable for the $$$. A large reason is they stamp the parts and never clean up the backside of the pressed steel. "fluff and buff+++" is the best description, not only have all the trigger group parts been sanded smooth, they have also been treated with smooth Kote & bp2000. First a liquid graphite, then a powdered graphite (ps, it make your 1911 a dream to shoot". We've been able to shoot soda cans at 100yrds. Imagine the power of 230gr with that accuracy. 

Approx $560 in upgrades or custom parts from Sierra Pappa. Best thing is you dont have to wait. I think I waited 6 months before the mags were available. This carbine does it all, home defense....230gr hollow points at approx 1150 fps...doesnt get any better. If you had to hunt hogs in an emergency,  this one will shine. The accuracy allows for amazing versatility. I haven't clocked my +P 180gr golden sabers, but with this accuracy,  I doubt any deer would still be standing. Not ideal, but one caliber that will defend your life, feed you and fill your sidearm. Check out how big 45 hollow points open up to. This caliber was a beast when only fmj was available, with today's hollow points opening to 3/4"++........plus you're getting 9mm speeds at a minimum, depending on the ammo its 9mm+P or +P+ velocities. 

All this in a light mobile package.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Desantis NY Undercover brown leather shoulder holster Sig P220/226/229
postcontent:
I have a barely used Desantis NY Undercover brown leather shoulder holster with double mag pouch made for the Sig P220/226/229 pistols.  All three fit great in it, it is a horizontal carry holster, and you can get different holsters to go on the rig for various pistols.  

This model does not have belt tie downs, though you can buy them for it.  I never found the need, when loaded everything lays pretty flat against the body and I had no trouble concealing comfortable a full size Sig P226 under a sweater with this.  

It's a very nice classy brown leather, the shoulder straps are thin but wide and supportive.  I was actually surprised at how well it all fit and was very comfortable, but I no longer need it.

It is a right hand model.

I got mine from Optics Planet for about $110 brand new, and I've worn it probably a dozen times, always on top of other shirts.

I'll sell for $50, plus $5 if you want me to ship it.  The photo included is stock, no matter what I did I couldn't get a good photo of mine, but it's in like new condition with only a little gun oil on the inside of the holster, as it should be.

I'm in Millbury, so I can meet anywhere fairly nearby, Worcester, Auburn, etc.

I'd also take a comparable quality leather holster for a full size 1911 in trade, brown or black doesn't matter, right hand.

CASH or POSTAL MONEY ORDER (if shipping) ONLY please. I will NOT accept Paypal.  I'm selling this very fine holster at far below it's new purchase price and I'm not driving all over the state to unload it.  I'm perfectly happy shipping it, but no, I'm not going to come meet you on the Cape or in the Berkshires so you can look at it.  I'll send you as many pictures as you want, but, no.  Thanks.

postcontent:
I thought I would never sell this gun, but I'm having some car troubles, and it's got to go.  



Up for sale is a 1968 Remmington 870 Wingmaster pump in 12 gauge with aftermarket engraving.  This is not some run of the mill express...it's a wing master and has the chrome carrier on the bottom that many people consider to be a much higher quality gun that what is made today due to the quality of finishing and quality of metal used in the build during that era.   The engraving is on both sides and top of the receiver, as well as the trigger guard and the original barrel.  It has the very sought after 870 trap wood with an 11 inch forearm (standard is 8 1/2) and high cheek buttstock with amazing figuring throughout as you can see.  The gun comes in a Zeigel Aluminum case with a later model Rem Choke 28" Vent Rib VR dual bead barrel and 8 chokes.  The chokes range from modified all the way to super full trap for those sharpshooters out there.  Althought it's not a 100 point gun, it's definitely in the high 90's and is by far the best looking 870 I've seen in person, and would make a great Christmas present, wedding present, or even something for that recent Grad.  



Factory engraved guns of this era go for $3-$8K if you can find them, and it will take you a good while to find another 870 that is as nice as this one, so I won't entertain lowballers or trades.  



Contact me for close up images of the engraving and wood, as well as a list of  the chokes included, and with any other questions.  I'm in the Denton area.

The SUB-2000 is a self-loading carbine for pistol cartridges. Different versions of the SUB-2000 will accept most modern handgun magazines; see below for a complete list. The SUB-2000 has a greatly enhanced accuracy and extended range compared to a handgun. The superior precision is also very useful against small or partially covered targets at shorter range. The amount of training to master the SUB-2000 is only a fraction of that required for a handgun. The SUB-2000 has been developed from our highly successful SUB-9 rifle. Although retaining some features of the old rifle, the SUB-2000 is a completely new design. Emphasis has been put on consumer safety, but without impeding the performance. Polymers are used to a large extent, resulting in increased durability and reduced price. The SUB-2000 is available in 9 mm Luger or .40 S&W calibers.

The bolt can be locked in the rear position by the operating handle. The main safety is of protected push bolt type disconnecting the trigger bar and interlocking the hammer and sear. By rotating the barrel upwards and back, the SUB-2000 can be reduced to a size of 16" x 7" to facilitate secure storage and utilize the internal deployment lock which is operated by a proprietary key. The rear sight is of aperture type and the fluorescent front sight can be adjusted for windage and elevation. The SUB-2000 can easily be disassembled for cleaning or inspection without tools.

The .40 SUB-2000 can be configured in the following magazine types: GLK22, GLK23, BERETTA96, S&W4006, SIG226.

THIS GUN IS IN HIGH DEMAND AND IS HARD TO COME BY. CALL US TODAY AT REDACTED OR COME IN AND SEE IT FOR YOURSELF AT US MONEY SHOPS IN CLEVELAND, TN.  ASK FOR JOHN

Get your friends or co-workers together for a quality firearms training course that meets the requirements for Ohio's CCW license.  We teach CCW classes all over northwest Ohio. 

We are a team of 2 NRA Certified Instructors with extensive backgrounds in firearms training and legal expertise. Our classes are typically held on Saturdays from 8 am to 8 pm. We also have access to several shooting ranges in Northwest Ohio or can use a private range from your group.

Our class provides in depth training and hands-on instruction in pistol handling, field stripping, cleaning, malfunction drills, shooting practice and defensive shooting drills. We also provide expertise and experience in firearms laws that sets our course apart from the rest.

We prefer smaller classes (4-6 people) to ensure the best possible class for our students.
